properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 26 at 2:50PM PST until January 27 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 20 to 30 kt
and seas 12 to 16 feet at 16 seconds. For the Gale Watch,
south winds 25 to 35 kt and seas 12 to 15 feet at 15 seconds
possible.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Cape Flattery to Cape Shoalwater
out to 60 nm.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 1 PM PST Monday.
For the Gale Watch, from Monday afternoon through Monday
evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Watch is issued when the risk of gale force winds of 34 to
47 knots has significantly increased, but the specific timing
and/or location is still uncertain. It is intended to provide
additional lead time for mariners who may wish to consider
altering their plans.
